Source:  Personal Communication
Author:  MICALFE
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  In Whangaroa, Maunganui, in Northland, one always speaks of going for a swim in the tide. These places are silted up with mudflats: one cannot swim etc. when the tide is out, so `tide' and `sea' are identified.
